  "text": "where ∆(t) is the instantaneous age of the last successfully received update as defined above. We will use a graphical argument similar to [CITATION_1] to derive the average age at an individual end node. Since all link delays are i.i.d. for all nodes and packets, each end node i experiences statistically identical age processes and will have the same average age. Therefore, it suffices to focus on a single end user for the age analysis.",
